ion))\nmember_casual_facts\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-28T19:36:43.210936Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-04-28T19:36:43.21253Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-04-28T19:36:43.573243Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"#Number of ride per hour of day\nActive_hour <- combined_cyclistics %>%\n    group_by(hour_of_day,member_casual)%>%\n    summarise(number_of_rides = n(),)%>%\n    arrange(member_casual, hour_of_day)\nActive_hour","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-28T19:44:38.433641Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-04-28T19:44:38.43525Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-04-28T19:44:38.716298Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"#To get the summary of number of rides and their average duration in seconds in weekdays by mem.\nActive_week <- combined_cyclistics %>%\n    group_by(member_casual, day_of_week)%>%\n    summarise(number_of_rides = n(),average_duration = mean(ride_duration))%>%\n    arrange(member_casual, desc(number_of_rides), day_of_week)    \nActive_week","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-28T19:44:47.75524Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-04-28T19:44:47.756815Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-04-28T19:44:48.060333Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# To get the total number of member rider by rideable type\nall_trips_member<-member_only %>% \n  group_by(month,rideable_type) %>% \n  summarise(number_of_rides = n(), average_duration = mean(ride_duration)) %>% \n  arrange(month, rideable_type)\n\nall_trips_member","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-28T19:44:58.356366Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-04-28T19:44:58.357976Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-04-28T19:44:58.5611Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# To get and plot a chart showing the total number of member rider grouped by rideable type and month\nall_trips_member_month<-member_only %>% \n  group_by(rideable_type,month) %>% \n  summarise(number_of_rides = n(), average_duration = mean(ride_duration)) %>% \n  arrange( rideable_type, month)\n \nall_trips_member_month","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-28T19:45:04.036518Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-04-28T19:45:04.038299Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-04-28T19:45:04.232043Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"colnames(all_trips_member)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-28T19:45:13.475797Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-04-28T19:45:13.477603Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-04-28T19:45:13.495291Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# To get the total number of memberrider grouped by rideable type and days of the week\nall_trips_member_week<-member_only %>% \n  group_by(rideable_type, day_of_week) %>% \n  summarise(number_of_rides = n(), average_duration = mean(ride_duration)) %>% \n  arrange(rideable_type, day_of_week)\n  \nall_trips_member_week","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-28T19:45:20.573469Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-04-28T19:45:20.575212Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-04-28T19:45:20.786976Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# To get the total number of casual rider grouped by rideable type and month\nall_trips_casual_month<-casual_only %>% \n  group_by(rideable_type, month) %>% \n  summarise(number_of_rides = n(), average_duration = mean(ride_duration)) %>% \n  arrange(rideable_type, month) \n  \nall_trips_casual_month","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-28T19:45:25.478518Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-04-28T19:45:25.479999Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-04-28T19:45:26.760682Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":" # To get the total number of casual rider grouped by rideable type and days of the \nall_trips_casual_week<-casual_only %>% \n  group_by(rideable_type, day_of_week) %>% \n  summarise(number_of_rides = n(), average_duration = mean(ride_duration)) %>% \n  arrange(rideable_type, day_of_week)\n  \nall_trips_casual_week","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-28T19:45:32.196302Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-04-28T19:45:32.197823Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-04-28T19:45:32.36341Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"<p id=\"part6\"></p>\n<p style=\"font-family: Arials; font-size: 16px; font-style: bold; font-weight: bold; letter-spacing: 3px; color: #FF8C00\">SHARE</p>\n<hr style=\"height: 0.5px; border: 0; background-color: #808080\">\n\n\nGuiding questions\n\n‚óè Were you able to answer the question of how annual members and casual riders use Cyclistic bikes differently?\n\n 1. Yes from the insight gotten, it turns out that casual users tend to ride more on weekends (saturdays and sundays) and other weekdays and the members subscribers\n tends to ride more on weekdays(wednessday,tuesday,thursday,friday and monday) \n \n 2. Also the difference in the top 10 travel route for both casual users and membership subscribers was obvious.\n \n‚óè What story does your data tell?\n\n**Interesting stories indeed!!!**\n\n1. According to [A chicago bike blog](https://www.chicagobikeblog.com/blog/2018/9/21/the-best-time-to-ride-your-bike-is-now), Autumn is the best weather for cycling in chicago  this explains the reason while the highest number of trips by electric bike was recorded in September, October and November.\n\n2. Also it was clearly seen on the line graph that there was a rapid increase in the no of trip from 15 - 20 hours and its peak at about 17 hours. this numbers makes sense as  16 - 18 hours i.e 4pm - 6pm has been regarded by [Tripsavvy](https://www.tripsavvy.com/driving-in-chicago-what-you-need-to-know-4175905) as a rush hour hence there heavy traffic in that hour and this is a strong correlation with the increase in the use of bikes by that hour(15 - 18 hours).\n\n\n\n‚óè How do your findings relate to your original question?\n\n*The finding tells that how members riding habits are different from casual riders. And how marketing team can make strategy to influence them through digital media.\n‚óè Who is your audience? What is the best way to communicate with them?\n‚óè Can data visualization help you share your findings?\n‚óè Is your presentation accessible to your audience?\nKey tasks\n1. Determine the best way to share your findings.\n2. Create effective data visualizations.\n3. Present your findings.\n4. Ensure your work is accessible.\nDeliverable\nSupporting visualizations and key findings\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Interesting Visuals**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"#A line plot of number of rides against hour of day\noptions(repr.plot.width = 18, repr.plot.height = 10)\nggplot(Active_hour, aes(x = hour_of_day , y = number_of_rides)) + \n    geom_line(aes(color = member_casual, linetype = member_casual)) + \n    geom_point()\n    scale_color_manual(values = c(\"darkred\", \"steelblue\")) +\n    labs(title=\"rides by hour_of_day\", x = \"hour_of_day\", y = \"Number of Rides\")","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-28T20:59:15.642494Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-04-28T20:59:15.644499Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-04-28T20:59:16.340354Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"#To get the summary of number of rides and their average duration in seconds in weekdays by mem.\nggplot(Active_week, aes(x = day_of_week, y = number_of_rides, fill = member_casual)) +\n    geom_col(position = \"dodge\") + labs(title=\"Total Number of Members Rides by week\", x = \"week\", y = \"Number of Member Rides\") + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 60, hjust = 1))","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-04-28T20:59:32.200587Z","iopub.execute_